{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901590347,"sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfbbf1b001NupmuNJh5A7SRR","messageID":"msg_d7bfbb608001ah01l4WPSF7qV4","sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2fb6cfe29f374dc5b4fc7469","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n2: \n3: **Module:** docs\n4: **Language:** Markdown\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube 文档站补全架构设计文档与 API 参考文档，填补当前 `docs/docs/api-reference/` 目录为空、部分架构文档缺失的空白。目标是为开发者、运维人员和集成方提供完整的系统架构说明和 API 契约参考，使文档站达到可对外发布的完整度。\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In Scope\n14: \n15: 1. **API Reference — Control Plane (WorkloadManager API)**\n16: \n17:    `docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md` — WorkloadManager 控制平面 REST API 完整参考。\n18: \n19:    | 端点 | 方法 | 说明 |\n20:    |------|------|------|\n21:    | `/v1/code-interpreter` | POST | 创建 CodeInterpreter sandbox session |\n22:    | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` | DELETE | 删除 session（幂等） |\n23:    | `/v1/agent-runtime` | POST | 创建 AgentRuntime sandbox session |\n24:    | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{id}` | DELETE | 删除 AgentRuntime session |\n25:    | `/health` | GET | 健康检查 |\n26: \n27:    每个端点包含：请求参数、请求体 schema、响应体 schema、错误码、curl 示例。\n28: \n29: 2. **API Reference — Data Plane (Router API)**\n30: \n31:    `docs/docs/api-reference/data-plane.md` — Router 数据平面 REST API 完整参考。\n32: \n33:    | 端点 | 方法 | 说明 |\n34:    |------|------|------|\n35:    | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/` | POST | 通过 Router 代理执行代码 |\n36:    | `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/` | POST | 通过 Router 代理调用 Agent |\n37:    | `/api/execute` | POST | 沙箱内执行命令（PicoD 端点） |\n38:    | `/api/files` | POST | 上传文件到沙箱（JSON base64 / multipart） |\n39:    | `/api/files/{path}` | GET | 从沙箱下载文件（流式） |\n40:    | `/api/files` | GET | 列出沙箱文件 |\n41:    | `/health/live` | GET | Router 存活探针 |\n42:    | `/health/ready` | GET | Router 就绪探针 |\n43: \n44:    每个端点包含：路径参数、请求头（含 `x-agentcube-session-id`）、请求体、响应体、错误码、curl 示例。\n45: \n46: 3. **API Reference — CRDs**\n47: \n48:    `docs/docs/api-reference/crds.md` — Kubernetes CRD 完整参考。\n49: \n50:    | CRD | API Group | Version | Scope |\n51:    |-----|-----------|---------|-------|\n52:    | CodeInterpreter | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | Namespaced |\n53:    | AgentRuntime | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | Namespaced |\n54:    | Sandbox | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | Namespaced |\n55: \n56:    每个 CRD 包含：完整 YAML 示例、spec 字段表（名称、类型、必填、说明、默认值）、status 字段表、生命周期说明。使用自定义 MDX 组件 `K8sResource` 渲染。\n57: \n58: 4. **Architecture — 设计决策记录**\n59: \n60:    `docs/docs/architecture/design-decisions.md` — 关键架构设计决策及其权衡分析。\n61: \n62:    | 决策 | 选项 A | 选项 B | 选定 |\n63:    |------|--------|--------|------|\n64:    | 会话存储 | Redis | Valkey | Valkey（开源兼容） |\n65:    | 沙箱隔离 | 容器级 | VM 级 | 容器级（cgroups + namespaces） |\n66:    | 路由方式 | Session-aware proxy | Service mesh | Session-aware proxy（轻量） |\n67:    | 调度器 | 默认 K8s scheduler | Volcano vc-agent-scheduler | 默认（Volcano 可选） |\n68:    | 控制面协议 | REST + CRD | gRPC | REST + CRD（K8s 原生） |\n69: \n70: 5. **Architecture — 数据流详解**\n71: \n72:    `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` — 完整请求生命周期数据流。\n73: \n74:    - 新 session 创建流程（Client → Router → Redis → WorkloadManager → K8s API → Pod → Router）\n75:    - 已有 session 请求流程（Client → Router → Redis cache → Pod）\n76:    - Session 续期流程（Client → Router → Redis TTL extend）\n77:    - Session 过期清理流程（Agentd → Redis scan → K8s API delete）\n78:    - 文件上传/下载数据流\n79: \n80: 6. **Architecture — 安全模型**\n81: \n82:    `docs/docs/architecture/security.md` — 安全架构说明。\n83: \n84:    - JWT RS256 认证流程\n85:    - K8s TokenReview 集成\n86:    - RBAC 权限模型\n87:    - 沙箱网络隔离策略\n88:    - Secret 管理（K8s Secrets + 环境变量注入）\n89: \n90: ### Out of Scope\n91: \n92: - 文档站 i18n 中文翻译（由其他 AR 覆盖）\n93: - 文档站 CI/CD 部署流水线（AR-042 已覆盖）\n94: - Dify 插件集成文档（AR-036 已覆盖）\n95: - 版本化文档快照（AR-042 已覆盖框架）\n96: - 博客/新闻内容\n97: - 第三方集成文档（LangChain 等，由后续 AR 覆盖）\n98: \n99: ## Impact Analysis\n100: \n101: ### Dependencies\n102: \n103: | 依赖 | 来源 | 说明 |\n104: |------|------|------|\n105: | Docusaurus 3.x | `docs/` 已存在 | 文档站框架（AR-042 已搭建） |\n106: | `ApiEndpoint` MDX 组件 | `docs/src/components/ApiEndpoint/` 已存在 | API 端点渲染组件 |\n107: | `K8sResource` MDX 组件 | `docs/src/components/K8sResource/` 已存在 | CRD 渲染组件 |\n108: | Go 源码 `pkg/` | 本项目 | Router/WorkloadManager 实际 API 实现 |\n109: | CRD 定义 `manifests/` | 本项目 | CRD YAML 源文件 |\n110: | Python SDK | `sdk-python/` | 控制面/数据面客户端契约参考 |\n111: \n112: ### Affected Components\n113: \n114: | 文件/目录 | 状态 | 说明 |\n115: |-----------|------|------|\n116: | `docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md` | 新增 | WorkloadManager API 参考 |\n117: | `docs/docs/api-reference/data-plane.md` | 新增 | Router API 参考 |\n118: | `docs/docs/api-reference/crds.md` | 新增 | CRD 参考 |\n119: | `docs/docs/api-reference/_category_.json` | 新增 | API Reference 分类元数据 |\n120: | `docs/docs/architecture/design-decisions.md` | 新增 | 设计决策记录 |\n121: | `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` | 新增 | 数据流详解 |\n122: | `docs/docs/architecture/security.md` | 新增 | 安全模型 |\n123: | `docs/sidebars.ts` | 无变更 | 已声明 api-reference 分类 |\n124: | `pkg/router/` | 无变更 | 作为 API 信息来源 |\n125: | `pkg/workloadmanager/` | 无变更 | 作为 API 信息来源 |\n126: | `manifests/` | 无变更 | 作为 CRD 信息来源 |\n127: \n128: ### Risk Assessment\n129: \n130: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n131: |------|------|----------|\n132: | API 文档与实际实现不一致 | 高 | 以 Go 源码 `pkg/` 为真相源，逐端点核对路由注册和 handler 签名 |\n133: | CRD 字段遗漏或过时 | 中 | 从 `manifests/` 中的 CRD YAML 直接提取字段定义 |\n134: | 文档构建失败（MDX 组件引用错误） | 低 | 使用 `npm run build` 本地验证后再提交 |\n135: | 安全模型描述泄露敏感信息 | 中 | 仅描述架构模式，不包含实际密钥、证书或内部 URL |\n136: | 数据流图过于复杂难以理解 | 低 | 使用 Mermaid 序列图，每个流程独立图表 |\n137: \n138: ## Alternatives Considered\n139: \n140: ### 1. 手写 Markdown vs. OpenAPI/Swagger 自动生成（✅ 选定手写 Markdown + MDX 组件）\n141: \n142: **做法**：使用 Docusaurus 已有的 `ApiEndpoint` MDX 组件手写 API 文档，而非从 Go 代码生成 OpenAPI spec 再转换。\n143: \n144: **优点**：\n145: - 与现有文档风格一致（已有 architecture/user-guide 均为手写 Markdown）\n146: - `ApiEndpoint` 组件已实现，可直接使用\n147: - 可加入人类可读的解释性文字和示例\n148: - 无需引入额外的 OpenAPI 注解和生成工具链\n149: \n150: **缺点**：\n151: - API 变更时需手动同步文档\n152: - 无法自动验证文档与实现的一致性\n153: \n154: **决策**：采用手写方案。当前 API 端点数量有限（约 10 个），手动维护成本可控。未来 API 稳定后可考虑引入 OpenAPI 生成作为补充。\n155: \n156: ### 2. 单文件 vs. 分文件 API 参考（✅ 选定分文件）\n157: \n158: **做法**：将 API 参考拆分为 `control-plane.md`、`data-plane.md`、`crds.md` 三个文件，而非合并为单个 `api-reference.md`。\n159: \n160: **优点**：\n161: - 与 sidebar 结构一致（已声明三个子项）\n162: - 每个文件聚焦单一关注点，便于维护\n163: - 读者可按需导航，无需滚动长文档\n164: \n165: **缺点**：\n166: - 跨平面交互（如 session 创建后如何路由）需要在多处引用\n167: - 文件间可能存在少量重复（如认证说明）\n168: \n169: **决策**：采用分文件方案。sidebar 已定义此结构，且控制面/数据面/CRD 是三个独立的关注域。\n170: \n171: ### 3. Mermaid vs. 外部绘图工具（✅ 选定 Mermaid）\n172: \n173: **做法**：使用 Docusaurus 内置 Mermaid 支持绘制架构图和数据流图，而非使用外部工具生成图片。\n174: \n175: **优点**：\n176: - Docusaurus 已启用 `@docusaurus/theme-mermaid`\n177: - 图表作为代码存储在 Git 中，可 diff 和 review\n178: - 支持暗色主题自动适配\n179: - 无需管理图片文件\n180: \n181: **缺点**：\n182: - Mermaid 表达能力有限，复杂图可能渲染不佳\n183: - 不如专业绘图工具美观\n184: \n185: **决策**：采用 Mermaid。数据流图和安全模型图复杂度适中，Mermaid 序列图和流程图足以表达。\n186: \n187: ### 4. 设计决策文档化 vs. 代码注释（✅ 选定独立文档）\n188: \n189: **做法**：将架构设计决策记录为独立的 `design-decisions.md` 文档，而非仅保留在代码注释或 Git 提交信息中。\n190: \n191: **优点**：\n192: - 对读者可见，无需浏览代码历史\n193: - 集中呈现，便于新成员理解架构演进\n194: - 可作为 ADR（Architecture Decision Record）的轻量替代\n195: \n196: **缺点**：\n197: - 需要额外维护\n198: - 可能与代码实现产生 drift\n199: \n200: **决策**：采用独立文档。AgentCube 的架构决策（如 Valkey 选型、session-aware 路由、容器级隔离）是理解系统的核心背景，值得显式记录。\n201: \n202: ## Implementation Plan\n203: \n204: ### Phase 1: API Reference — Control Plane & Data Plane\n205: \n206: - [ ] 从 `pkg/router/` 提取 Router 端点定义，编写 `data-plane.md`\n207: - [ ] 从 `pkg/workloadmanager/` 提取 WorkloadManager 端点定义，编写 `control-plane.md`\n208: - [ ] 每个端点使用 `ApiEndpoint` MDX 组件渲染\n209: - [ ] 包含 curl 示例和响应示例\n210: \n211: ### Phase 2: API Reference — CRDs\n212: \n213: - [ ] 从 `manifests/` 提取 CRD YAML 定义\n214: - [ ] 编写 `crds.md`，为每个 CRD 使用 `K8sResource` MDX 组件\n215: - [ ] 包含完整 YAML 示例和字段说明表\n216: \n217: ### Phase 3: Architecture Supplements\n218: \n219: - [ ] 编写 `design-decisions.md`（5 个关键决策）\n220: - [ ] 编写 `data-flow.md`（5 个 Mermaid 序列图）\n221: - [ ] 编写 `security.md`（认证、RBAC、隔离）\n222: \n223: ### Phase 4: Verification\n224: \n225: - [ ] `cd docs && npm run build` — 构建通过，无 broken links\n226: - [ ] 本地 `npm run serve` 预览，确认渲染正确\n227: - [ ] 与 Go 源码交叉核对 API 端点完整性\n228: \n229: ## Acceptance Criteria\n230: \n231: - [ ] `docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md` 存在且包含所有 WorkloadManager 端点\n232: - [ ] `docs/docs/api-reference/data-plane.md` 存在且包含所有 Router 端点\n233: - [ ] `docs/docs/api-reference/crds.md` 存在且包含 CodeInterpreter、AgentRuntime、Sandbox 三个 CRD\n234: - [ ] `docs/docs/api-reference/_category_.json` 存在\n235: - [ ] `docs/docs/architecture/design-decisions.md` 存在且包含至少 5 个关键决策\n236: - [ ] `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` 存在且包含至少 5 个 Mermaid 序列图\n237: - [ ] `docs/docs/architecture/security.md` 存在且覆盖认证、RBAC、隔离\n238: - [ ] 所有新文档使用正确的 frontmatter（sidebar_position、title、description、keywords）\n239: - [ ] `cd docs && npm run build` 成功，无 warnings 或 errors\n240: - [ ] API 端点与 Go 源码 `pkg/` 中的路由注册一致\n241: - [ ] CRD 字段与 `manifests/` 中的 YAML 定义一致\n242: - [ ] 所有 curl 示例语法正确\n243: - [ ] 所有 Mermaid 图在 Docusaurus 中正确渲染\n244: \n245: ## Status\n246: \n247: - [ ] Proposal review\n248: - [ ] Implementation\n249: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 249 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n**Module:** docs\n**Language:** Markdown\n**Size:** M\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 文档站补全架构设计文档与 API 参考文档，填补当前 `docs/docs/api-reference/` 目录为空、部分架构文档缺失的空白。目标是为开发者、运维人员和集成方提供完整的系统架构说明和 API 契约参考，使文档站达到可对外发布的完整度。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **API Reference — Control Plane (WorkloadManager API)**\n\n   `docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md` — WorkloadManager 控制平面 REST API 完整参考。\n\n   | 端点 | 方法 | 说明 |\n   |------|------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775901590337,"end":1775901590345}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901591641,"sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfbc3d0001ge4rHj6QV6qNFC","messageID":"msg_d7bfbb608001ah01l4WPSF7qV4","sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b791f7c5c57c4b569ad5eec0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 1\n3: title: Architecture Overview\n4: description: High-level system architecture of AgentCube\n5: keywords: [architecture, system-design, components, overview]\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Architecture Overview\n9: \n10: AgentCube is built as a set of loosely coupled microservices running on Kubernetes, communicating through a shared session store and the Kubernetes API.\n11: \n12: ## System Architecture\n13: \n14: ```\n15: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n16: │                        Kubernetes Cluster                         │\n17: │                                                                    │\n18: │  ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n19: │  │   Client     │────▶│           Router (Deployment)        │    │\n20: │  │  / SDK / CLI │     │         Session-Aware Proxy          │    │\n21: │  └─────────────┘     └──────────────┬───────────────────────┘    │\n22: │                                     │                             │\n23: │                            ┌────────▼────────┐                   │\n24: │                            │  Redis / Valkey  │                   │\n25: │                            │  (Session Store) │                   │\n26: │                            └────────┬─────────┘                   │\n27: │                                     │                             │\n28: │                   ┌─────────────────▼──────────────────┐          │\n29: │                   │     WorkloadManager (Controller)    │          │\n30: │                   │   - Sandbox Lifecycle Management    │          │\n31: │                   │   - CRD Reconciliation              │          │\n32: │                   │   - Resource Provisioning           │          │\n33: │                   └─────────────────┬──────────────────┘          │\n34: │                                     │                             │\n35: │                   ┌─────────────────▼──────────────────┐          │\n36: │                   │         Kubernetes API              │          │\n37: │                   │   - CRDs, Pods, Secrets, etc.       │          │\n38: │                   └─────────────────┬──────────────────┘          │\n39: │                                     │                             │\n40: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────▼──────────────────────┐     │\n41: │  │              Sandbox Pods                                │     │\n42: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐      │     │\n43: │  │  │  Sandbox 1  │  │  Sandbox 2  │  │  Sandbox N  │      │     │\n44: │  │  │  (PicoD)    │  │  (PicoD)    │  │  (PicoD)    │      │     │\n45: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘      │     │\n46: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n47: │                                                                    │\n48: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n49: │  │              Agentd (Idle Cleanup Controller)              │    │\n50: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n51: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ## Design Principles\n55: \n56: 1. **Kubernetes-Native**: Built on CRDs and controller-runtime, integrating with K8s ecosystem\n57: 2. **Session-Aware**: All routing decisions are based on session state stored in Redis/Valkey\n58: 3. **Isolation-First**: Each agent workload runs in its own isolated sandbox\n59: 4. **Event-Driven**: Components react to Kubernetes events and session state changes\n60: 5. **Horizontally Scalable**: Router and WorkloadManager can scale independently\n61: \n62: ## Component Summary\n63: \n64: | Component | Type | Responsibility |\n65: |-----------|------|----------------|\n66: | **Router** | Deployment | HTTP proxy, session routing, load balancing |\n67: | **WorkloadManager** | Controller | Sandbox lifecycle, CRD reconciliation |\n68: | **Session Store** | StatefulSet/External | Session state, routing table |\n69: | **PicoD** | Sidecar/Daemon | Code execution inside sandboxes |\n70: | **Agentd** | Controller | Idle sandbox cleanup, resource reclamation |\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: 1. Client sends request to Router with session identifier\n75: 2. Router looks up session in Redis/Valkey to find target sandbox\n76: 3. If session exists, Router forwards request to sandbox\n77: 4. If no session, Router creates new session and signals WorkloadManager\n78: 5. WorkloadManager provisions sandbox pod via Kubernetes API\n79: 6. Once sandbox is ready, Router forwards request and caches routing info\n80: \n81: ## Next Steps\n82: \n83: - Dive into individual [Components](./components.md)\n84: - Learn about [Session Routing](./session-routing.md)\n85: - Understand [Sandbox Lifecycle](./sandbox-lifecycle.md)\n\n(End of file - total 85 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 1\ntitle: Architecture Overview\ndescription: High-level system architecture of AgentCube\nkeywords: [architecture, system-design, components, overview]\n---\n\n# Architecture Overview\n\nAgentCube is built as a set of loosely coupled microservices running on Kubernetes, communicating through a shared session store and the Kubernetes API.\n\n## System Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Kubernetes Cluster                         │\n│                                                                    │\n│  ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │   Client     │────▶│           Router (Deployment)        │    │\n│  │  / SDK / CLI │     │         Session-Aware Proxy          │    │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md","time":{"start":1775901591632,"end":1775901591639}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901592865,"sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfbc8df001ef1Y8HLkjxx9iA","messageID":"msg_d7bfbb608001ah01l4WPSF7qV4","sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b789707a59f4408e83f91362","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 2\n3: title: Components\n4: description: Deep dive into AgentCube's core components\n5: keywords: [components, router, workload-manager, picod, agentd]\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Components\n9: \n10: This page provides a deep dive into each core component of AgentCube.\n11: \n12: ## Router\n13: \n14: The Router is a session-aware HTTP proxy that directs incoming requests to the correct sandbox instance.\n15: \n16: ### Responsibilities\n17: \n18: - Accept HTTP requests from clients (SDK, CLI, direct API)\n19: - Look up session information in Redis/Valkey\n20: - Route requests to the appropriate sandbox pod\n21: - Create new sessions when none exists\n22: - Load balance across multiple WorkloadManager instances\n23: \n24: ### Technical Details\n25: \n26: - Built with Go using the Gin HTTP framework\n27: - Listens on port 8080 by default\n28: - Maintains a local cache of session-to-pod mappings\n29: - Supports JWT authentication for API requests\n30: \n31: ### Key Endpoints\n32: \n33: | Endpoint | Method | Description |\n34: |----------|--------|-------------|\n35: | `/api/v1/execute` | POST | Execute code in a sandbox |\n36: | `/api/v1/sessions` | GET | List active sessions |\n37: | `/api/v1/health` | GET | Health check |\n38: \n39: ## WorkloadManager\n40: \n41: The WorkloadManager is a Kubernetes controller that manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources.\n42: \n43: ### Responsibilities\n44: \n45: - Watch for CRD changes (CodeInterpreter, AgentRuntime, Sandbox)\n46: - Reconcile desired state with actual cluster state\n47: - Create and manage sandbox pods\n48: - Handle resource provisioning (secrets, configmaps, volumes)\n49: - Report status back to CRD instances\n50: \n51: ### Technical Details\n52: \n53: - Built with Go using controller-runtime\n54: - Watches multiple CRD types in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n55: - Uses leader election for high availability\n56: - Integrates with Redis/Valkey for session state updates\n57: \n58: ### Reconciliation Loop\n59: \n60: ```\n61: Watch CRD → Compare desired vs actual → Create/Update/Delete pods → Update CRD status\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## PicoD\n65: \n66: PicoD is an optional daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to handle code execution requests.\n67: \n68: ### Responsibilities\n69: \n70: - Receive code execution requests from the Router\n71: - Sanitize and execute code in a controlled environment\n72: - Enforce resource limits (CPU, memory, time)\n73: - Return execution results (output, exit code, errors)\n74: \n75: ### Technical Details\n76: \n77: - Lightweight Go binary\n78: - Listens on a port within the sandbox pod\n79: - Supports multiple languages (Python, Go, etc.)\n80: - Uses OS-level isolation (cgroups, namespaces)\n81: \n82: ## Agentd\n83: \n84: Agentd is an idle cleanup controller that reclaims unused sandbox resources.\n85: \n86: ### Responsibilities\n87: \n88: - Monitor sandbox activity via session store\n89: - Identify idle sandboxes exceeding the configured timeout\n90: - Gracefully terminate idle sandboxes\n91: - Clean up associated Kubernetes resources\n92: \n93: ### Technical Details\n94: \n95: - Runs as a Kubernetes controller\n96: - Configurable idle timeout (default: 30 minutes)\n97: - Periodic check interval (default: 5 minutes)\n98: - Graceful shutdown with configurable drain period\n99: \n100: ## Session Store (Redis/Valkey)\n101: \n102: The session store is the central state management component.\n103: \n104: ### Responsibilities\n105: \n106: - Store session-to-pod mappings\n107: - Track session TTL and activity timestamps\n108: - Support pub/sub for cross-component communication\n109: - Provide atomic operations for session creation/deletion\n110: \n111: ### Data Model\n112: \n113: ```\n114: Key: session:{sessionId}\n115: Value: {\n116:   \"podName\": \"sandbox-abc123\",\n117:   \"podIP\": \"10.0.0.5\",\n118:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n119:   \"lastActiveAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:05:00Z\",\n120:   \"status\": \"active\"\n121: }\n122: ```\n123: \n124: ## Next Steps\n125: \n126: - Learn about [Session Routing](./session-routing.md)\n127: - Understand [Sandbox Lifecycle](./sandbox-lifecycle.md)\n\n(End of file - total 127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 2\ntitle: Components\ndescription: Deep dive into AgentCube's core components\nkeywords: [components, router, workload-manager, picod, agentd]\n---\n\n# Components\n\nThis page provides a deep dive into each core component of AgentCube.\n\n## Router\n\nThe Router is a session-aware HTTP proxy that directs incoming requests to the correct sandbox instance.\n\n### Responsibilities\n\n- Accept HTTP requests from clients (SDK, CLI, direct API)\n- Look up session information in Redis/Valkey\n- Route requests to the appropriate sandbox pod","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/architecture/components.md","time":{"start":1775901592856,"end":1775901592863}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901594163,"sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfbcda6001AyLB4CrUZD07fI","messageID":"msg_d7bfbb608001ah01l4WPSF7qV4","sessionID":"ses_28406c2a0ffebaRCAelXVCmpr2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6001c15c95614848864efe42","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 1\n3: title: Control Plane API\n4: description: WorkloadManager REST API reference for sandbox lifecycle management\n5: keywords: [api, control-plane, workload-manager, rest, sandbox]\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Control Plane API\n9: \n10: The Control Plane API is exposed by the **WorkloadManager** service. It provides REST endpoints for creating, querying, extending, and deleting sandbox sessions.\n11: \n12: **Base URL:** `http://<workloadmanager-host>:<port>` (default port: `8081`)\n13: \n14: All endpoints return JSON responses.\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Sandbox Creation\n19: \n20: <ApiEndpoint method=\"POST\" path=\"/api/v1/sandboxes\" description=\"Create a new sandbox session (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter)\" auth=\"bearer\" />\n21: \n22: Creates a new sandbox session by instantiating the specified CRD (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter). The WorkloadManager reconciles the CRD, provisions a sandbox pod, and returns session information.\n23: \n24: ### Request Body\n25: \n26: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n27: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n28: | `kind` | string | Yes | Resource type: `\"AgentRuntime\"` or `\"CodeInterpreter\"` |\n29: | `name` | string | Yes | Name of the CRD instance to instantiate |\n30: | `namespace` | string | Yes | Kubernetes namespace where the CRD exists |\n31: \n32: ### Request Example\n33: \n34: ```json\n35: {\n36:   \"kind\": \"CodeInterpreter\",\n37:   \"name\": \"python-sandbox\",\n38:   \"namespace\": \"default\"\n39: }\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Response — 201 Created\n43: \n44: | Field | Type | Description |\n45: |-------|------|-------------|\n46: | `sessionId` | string | Unique session identifier |\n47: | `sandboxId` | string | Kubernetes UID of the sandbox pod |\n48: | `sandboxName` | string | Name of the sandbox pod |\n49: | `entryPoints` | array | List of accessible endpoints within the sandbox |\n50: \n51: **EntryPoint schema:**\n52: \n53: | Field | Type | Description |\n54: |-------|------|-------------|\n55: | `path` | string | URL path prefix |\n56: | `protocol` | string | Protocol: `\"HTTP\"` or `\"HTTPS\"` |\n57: | `endpoint` | string | Full endpoint URL |\n58: \n59: ### Response Example\n60: \n61: ```json\n62: {\n63:   \"sessionId\": \"sess-a1b2c3d4\",\n64:   \"sandboxId\": \"uid-12345\",\n65:   \"sandboxName\": \"python-sandbox-abc123\",\n66:   \"entryPoints\": [\n67:     {\n68:       \"path\": \"/api\",\n69:       \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n70:       \"endpoint\": \"http://10.0.0.5:8080/api\"\n71:     }\n72:   ]\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Error Responses\n77: \n78: | Status Code | Error Code | Description |\n79: |-------------|------------|-------------|\n80: | 400 | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Validation failed — missing or invalid `kind`, `name`, or `namespace` |\n81: | 404 | `TEMPLATE_NOT_FOUND` | The specified CRD instance does not exist in the given namespace |\n82: | 500 | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Internal server error — sandbox provisioning failed |\n83: \n84: ### curl Example\n85: \n86: ```bash\n87: curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes \\\n88:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n89:   -d '{\n90:     \"kind\": \"CodeInterpreter\",\n91:     \"name\": \"python-sandbox\",\n92:     \"namespace\": \"default\"\n93:   }'\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ## Sandbox Query\n99: \n100: ### Get Sandbox by Session ID\n101: \n102: <ApiEndpoint method=\"GET\" path=\"/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID\" description=\"Get detailed status of a specific sandbox session\" auth=\"bearer\" />\n103: \n104: Returns the current status of a sandbox session, including lifecycle timestamps, entry points, and idle/expiry information.\n105: \n106: ### Path Parameters\n107: \n108: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n109: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n110: | `sessionID` | string | Yes | The session ID returned during sandbox creation |\n111: \n112: ### Response — 200 OK\n113: \n114: | Field | Type | Description |\n115: |-------|------|-------------|\n116: | `sessionId` | string | Session identifier |\n117: | `sandboxName` | string | Sandbox pod name |\n118: | `sandboxId` | string | Sandbox pod UID |\n119: | `status` | string | Current status: `\"running\"`, `\"pending\"`, `\"terminated\"` |\n120: | `createdAt` | string | ISO 8601 timestamp of session creation |\n121: | `expiresAt` | string | ISO 8601 timestamp of session expiration |\n122: | `lastActivityAt` | string | ISO 8601 timestamp of last activity |\n123: | `timeToExpiry` | string | Duration until session expires (optional) |\n124: | `timeToIdle` | string | Duration until session is considered idle (optional) |\n125: | `isExpired` | boolean | Whether the session has expired |\n126: | `isIdle` | boolean | Whether the session is idle |\n127: | `entryPoints` | array | List of sandbox entry points |\n128: \n129: ### Response Example\n130: \n131: ```json\n132: {\n133:   \"sessionId\": \"sess-a1b2c3d4\",\n134:   \"sandboxName\": \"python-sandbox-abc123\",\n135:   \"sandboxId\": \"uid-12345\",\n136:   \"status\": \"running\",\n137:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n138:   \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-01T08:00:00Z\",\n139:   \"lastActivityAt\": \"2024-01-01T02:30:00Z\",\n140:   \"timeToExpiry\": \"5h30m0s\",\n141:   \"timeToIdle\": \"27m30s\",\n142:   \"isExpired\": false,\n143:   \"isIdle\": false,\n144:   \"entryPoints\": [\n145:     {\n146:       \"path\": \"/api\",\n147:       \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n148:       \"endpoint\": \"http://10.0.0.5:8080/api\"\n149:     }\n150:   ]\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Error Responses\n155: \n156: | Status Code | Description |\n157: |-------------|-------------|\n158: | 400 | `sessionID` is missing or empty |\n159: | 404 | Session not found |\n160: | 500 | Internal server error |\n161: \n162: ### curl Example\n163: \n164: ```bash\n165: curl http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes/sess-a1b2c3d4\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ### List Sandboxes\n171: \n172: <ApiEndpoint method=\"GET\" path=\"/api/v1/sandboxes\" description=\"List all sandbox sessions with optional filtering\" auth=\"bearer\" />\n173: \n174: Returns a list of all active sandbox sessions. Supports filtering by namespace and status.\n175: \n176: ### Query Parameters\n177: \n178: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n179: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n180: | `namespace` | string | No | Filter by Kubernetes namespace |\n181: | `status` | string | No | Filter by sandbox status (e.g., `\"running\"`) |\n182: \n183: ### Response — 200 OK\n184: \n185: | Field | Type | Description |\n186: |-------|------|-------------|\n187: | `total` | integer | Total number of matching sandboxes |\n188: | `items` | array | List of sandbox items |\n189: \n190: **SandboxListItem schema:**\n191: \n192: | Field | Type | Description |\n193: |-------|------|-------------|\n194: | `sessionId` | string | Session identifier |\n195: | `sandboxName` | string | Sandbox pod name |\n196: | `workloadName` | string | Workload (CRD) name |\n197: | `namespace` | string | Kubernetes namespace |\n198: | `kind` | string | Resource type |\n199: | `status` | string | Current status |\n200: | `createdAt` | string | Creation timestamp |\n201: | `expiresAt` | string | Expiration timestamp |\n202: | `lastActivityAt` | string | Last activity timestamp |\n203: | `timeToExpiry` | string | Duration until expiry (optional) |\n204: | `timeToIdle` | string | Duration until idle (optional) |\n205: | `isExpired` | boolean | Whether expired |\n206: | `isIdle` | boolean | Whether idle |\n207: \n208: ### Response Example\n209: \n210: ```json\n211: {\n212:   \"total\": 2,\n213:   \"items\": [\n214:     {\n215:       \"sessionId\": \"sess-a1b2c3d4\",\n216:       \"sandboxName\": \"python-sandbox-abc123\",\n217:       \"workloadName\": \"python-sandbox\",\n218:       \"namespace\": \"default\",\n219:       \"kind\": \"CodeInterpreter\",\n220:       \"status\": \"running\",\n221:       \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n222:       \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-01T08:00:00Z\",\n223:       \"lastActivityAt\": \"2024-01-01T02:30:00Z\",\n224:       \"timeToExpiry\": \"5h30m0s\",\n225:       \"isExpired\": false,\n226:       \"isIdle\": false\n227:     }\n228:   ]\n229: }\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ### curl Example\n233: \n234: ```bash\n235: # List all sandboxes\n236: curl http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes\n237: \n238: # Filter by namespace\n239: curl \"http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes?namespace=default\"\n240: \n241: # Filter by status\n242: curl \"http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes?status=running\"\n243: ```\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## Sandbox Deletion\n248: \n249: <ApiEndpoint method=\"DELETE\" path=\"/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID\" description=\"Delete a sandbox session (idempotent)\" auth=\"bearer\" />\n250: \n251: Deletes a sandbox session and its associated Kubernetes resources. This operation is idempotent — deleting a non-existent session returns 404 but is treated as success from a cleanup perspective.\n252: \n253: ### Path Parameters\n254: \n255: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n256: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n257: | `sessionID` | string | Yes | The session ID to delete |\n258: \n259: ### Response — 200 OK\n260: \n261: ```json\n262: {\n263:   \"message\": \"sandbox deleted successfully\",\n264:   \"sessionId\": \"sess-a1b2c3d4\"\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### Error Responses\n269: \n270: | Status Code | Description |\n271: |-------------|-------------|\n272: | 404 | Session not found (may already be deleted) |\n273: | 500 | Internal server error — deletion failed |\n274: \n275: ### curl Example\n276: \n277: ```bash\n278: curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes/sess-a1b2c3d4\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## Sandbox TTL Extension\n284: \n285: <ApiEndpoint method=\"POST\" path=\"/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend\" description=\"Extend the TTL of an active sandbox session\" auth=\"bearer\" />\n286: \n287: Extends the expiration time of an active sandbox session. The extension duration must be positive and cannot exceed 24 hours. Cannot extend an already-expired session.\n288: \n289: ### Path Parameters\n290: \n291: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n292: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n293: | `sessionID` | string | Yes | The session ID to extend |\n294: \n295: ### Request Body\n296: \n297: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n298: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n299: | `extensionDuration` | string (duration) | Yes | Duration to extend by (e.g., `\"1h\"`, `\"30m\"`) |\n300: \n301: ### Request Example\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"extensionDuration\": \"2h\"\n306: }\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ### Response — 200 OK\n310: \n311: | Field | Type | Description |\n312: |-------|------|-------------|\n313: | `sessionId` | string | Session identifier |\n314: | `newExpiry` | string | New expiration timestamp (ISO 8601) |\n315: \n316: ### Response Example\n317: \n318: ```json\n319: {\n320:   \"sessionId\": \"sess-a1b2c3d4\",\n321:   \"newExpiry\": \"2024-01-01T10:00:00Z\"\n322: }\n323: ```\n324: \n325: ### Error Responses\n326: \n327: | Status Code | Description |\n328: |-------------|-------------|\n329: | 400 | Invalid request — `extensionDuration` missing, not positive, or exceeds 24 hours |\n330: | 404 | Session not found |\n331: | 410 | Session has already expired and cannot be extended |\n332: | 500 | Internal server error |\n333: \n334: ### curl Example\n335: \n336: ```bash\n337: curl -X POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sandboxes/sess-a1b2c3d4/extend \\\n338:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n339:   -d '{\"extensionDuration\": \"2h\"}'\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ## Health Checks\n345: \n346: ### Liveness Probe\n347: \n348: <ApiEndpoint method=\"GET\" path=\"/health/live\" description=\"Liveness probe — returns ok if the process is running\" auth=\"none\" />\n349: \n350: Returns a simple health check response. Used by Kubernetes liveness probes.\n351: \n352: ### Response — 200 OK\n353: \n354: ```json\n355: {\n356:   \"status\": \"ok\"\n357: }\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ### curl Example\n361: \n362: ```bash\n363: curl http://localhost:8081/health/live\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ### Readiness Probe\n369: \n370: <ApiEndpoint method=\"GET\" path=\"/health/ready\" description=\"Readiness probe — returns ok if the service is ready to accept requests\" auth=\"none\" />\n371: \n372: Returns a readiness check response. Used by Kubernetes readiness probes to determine if the service can accept traffic.\n373: \n374: ### Response — 200 OK\n375: \n376: ```json\n377: {\n378:   \"status\": \"ok\"\n379: }\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ### curl Example\n383: \n384: ```bash\n385: curl http://localhost:8081/health/ready\n386: ```\n\n(End of file - total 386 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 1\ntitle: Control Plane API\ndescription: WorkloadManager REST API reference for sandbox lifecycle management\nkeywords: [api, control-plane, workload-manager, rest, sandbox]\n---\n\n# Control Plane API\n\nThe Control Plane API is exposed by the **WorkloadManager** service. It provides REST endpoints for creating, querying, extending, and deleting sandbox sessions.\n\n**Base URL:** `http://<workloadmanager-host>:<port>` (default port: `8081`)\n\nAll endpoints return JSON responses.\n\n---\n\n## Sandbox Creation\n\n<ApiEndpoint method=\"POST\" path=\"/api/v1/sandboxes\" description=\"Create a new sandbox session (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter)\" auth=\"bearer\" />","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/docs/api-reference/control-plane.md","time":{"start":1775901594153,"end":1775901594161}}}}
